# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SONATA SERVER - OPTIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# IMPORTANT: Most settings are now stored in the database and can be configured
# via the Admin Settings UI (admin users only).
#
# The server will automatically generate a secure SECRET_KEY on first startup.
#
# Only DATABASE_URL needs to be set here if you want to use PostgreSQL.
# All other settings are optional and managed through the web UI.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Database (optional - SQLite is default) ───────────────────────────────────
# Set to use PostgreSQL instead of SQLite (default: sqlite:///db.sqlite3)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/sonata

# ── Advanced: Override SECRET_KEY (not recommended) ─────────────────────────
# If set, this will override the auto-generated SECRET_KEY stored in DB
# SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ALL OTHER SETTINGS ARE CONFIGURABLE VIA ADMIN UI:
#   - Server name, debug mode
#   - User registration settings
#   - CORS origins
#   - JWT token lifetimes
#   - Rate limiting
#   - LDAP authentication
#   - Encryption keys
#
# Navigate to: Admin → Server Settings after logging in as admin
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
